  "response": "{\"type\":\"thread.started\",\"thread_id\":\"019e42fc-1220-7e01-8431-53182ca44db5\"}\n{\"type\":\"turn.started\"}\n{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_0\",\"type\":\"agent_message\",\"text\":\"The relevant finding is `crime_00025` on `src/assets/check-icon.png`:\\n\\n> `dimensions: 32 × 32 px (≤ 64 threshold both sides)`\\n\\nThat means the existing check icon is an icon-sized PNG locked to a single 32×32 pixel raster. Copying that pattern for a new status indicator would bake in the same limitation: it can blur or look soft on high-DPI screens, and any future size variant needs another exported bitmap.\\n\\nA new SVG indicator is the better starting point because status icons are usually simple shapes. SVG will scale cleanly at every size and DPI, can often ship in fewer bytes, and is easier to recolor or adjust without regenerating raster assets.\"}}\n{\"type\":\"turn.completed\",\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":29431,\"cached_input_tokens\":12160,\"output_tokens\":201,\"reasoning_output_tokens\":48}}\n",
